ünstelt“ habe, dann trifft er damit letzten Endes sehr genau, was hier passiert: Die Entdeckung der Literatur als Praxis einer diskursivierten Liebe, die sich in jedem Augenblick aufs Neue erzählen muss.  aThis book contains love correspondences between Otto von Bismarck, Adalbert Stifter, Leopold von Sacher-Masoch, Ernst Haeckel and their respective wives and lovers. It counters the transient nature of love by extending the correspondence to other areas: realism – constituting much more than just a literary and artistic program – is here presented as a project undertaken by these 19th-century couples with the aim of facilitating their lives and keeping alive the romantic impulse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aLove-letters in literature. 0aLove-lettersxHistory. 0aLove-letterszGermany. 4aBriefkultur. 4aLiebesdiskurse. 4aLiteratur und Leben. 4aRealismus. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aEpistolary Culture.  aLove Letters.  aRealism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311027208640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027229140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110272291423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110272291/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014